---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Advisory — One skill set, four formats | Tom Vranas"
  description="Fractional COO and Chief of Staff, operating system installation, transition and integration sprints, and executive coaching — monthly retainers or defined sprints."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Ways to Work Together</p>
      <h1 style="margin-top: 0.9rem;">One skill set, four formats.</h1>

      <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        Every engagement is the same underlying motion &mdash; diagnose, fix, grow, systematize
        &mdash; at different depths. Pick the depth that matches your situation. All of them end
        the same way: with your team running it, not me.
      </p>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 3rem;">Engagements</h2>

      <div class="proof-blocks" style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">
        <div class="proof-block">
          <h3>Fractional COO / Chief of Staff.</h3>
          <p>
            The full second seat, part-time. I sit beside the CEO, own the operating cadence, and
            run the machine while you run the vision. For companies between &ldquo;founder does
            everything&rdquo; and &ldquo;ready for a full-time COO.&rdquo;
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="proof-block">
          <h3>Operating system installation.</h3>
          <p>
            Implementing EOS or an equivalent rhythm &mdash; scorecards, meeting cadence,
            accountability structure &mdash; so the business runs on data and process instead of
            heroics. For leadership teams who know they need it and haven&rsquo;t been able to
            make it stick.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="proof-block">
          <h3>Transition and integration sprints.</h3>
          <p>
            Defined-scope engagements for post-close integrations, new-leader 90-day triage, or a
            stalled function that needs rebuilding &mdash; what to audit first, what to delegate
            immediately, where the financial hygiene problems hide. Defined scope, defined
            timeline, hand-off to your permanent team.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="proof-block">
          <h3>Executive coaching.</h3>
          <p>
            One-on-one work with founders and operating leaders &mdash; usually the leader
            stepping into a bigger seat than they&rsquo;ve held before. Direct, practical, built
            on having actually sat in the seats. No personality assessments, no inspiration.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 3rem;">Format</h2>
      <p style="margin-top: 0.7rem;">
        Monthly retainers or defined sprints. We look at your actual business and fix actual
        things.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="pull-quote" style="margin-top: 3rem;">
        &ldquo;Predictable systems and high-performing teams are the only durable competitive
        advantage. Everything else gets copied.&rdquo;
      </blockquote>

      <p style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">
        <a class="btn" href="/contact">Inquire about working together</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
